  "text": "The equivalence of the traveling wave and the finite difference solution of the ideal wave equation (given in (5) and (11), respectively) has been shown, for instance, in [CITATION_1] . Based on this functional equivalence, [CITATION_2] has been previously expanded without a formal derivation to a scattering junction with arbitrary port impedances, where (8) is used as a template for the expansion [CITATION_3] . The resulting FDTD model structure is illustrated in Figure 3 for a three-port junction. A comparison of the FDTD model structure in Figure 3 and the DWG scattering junction in Figure 2 reveals the functional similarities of the two methods. However, a formal, generalized, and unified derivation of the FDTD model structure without an explicit reference to the DWG method remains to be presented. This section presents such a derivation based on the equations of motion of the gas in a tube. Note that, because of the analogy between different physical domains, once the formulation is derived, it can be used in different domains as well. Therefore, the derivation below is not limited to the acoustical domain and the resulting structure can also be used in other domains.",
